news.title: No need for concern over Land Titling act: Andhra Pradesh minister
news.para: Addressing a gathering at patta distribution programme held here on Friday, the revenue minister said that the government had allotted house sites to 30 lakh people and provided help in construction in those lands.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh plans 1,000-acre township in Ayodhya
news.para: The 'New Ayodhya', for which the state government has already secured land, will be India's first vastu-based township, he said.

news.title: Dispute resolution cell to be operational at Odisha RERA
news.para: The platform, called conciliation and dispute resolute (CDR) cell, will allow interested homebuyers and promoters to initiate a conciliation process and arrive at a mutual decision without going to court.

news.title: Ghaziabad: House tax may rise by up to Rs 5,000 from April 2024
news.para: The circle rates in the city are determined as per road widths in the locality. If revised, the new taxation rate will range from Rs 3.5 per sq ft to Rs 4 per sq ft, up from the existing Rs 1.61 per sq ft to Rs 2.45 per sq ft.

news.title: Delhi-NCR air pollution: Centre bans non-essential construction work
news.para: Anticipating a prolonged period of severe air quality, the committee decided to implement GRAP Stage-III curbs ('severe' air quality index (AQI) range) immediately to prevent further deterioration.

news.title: Goa: GIDC to e-auction 16 plots at Verna under new norms
news.para: The GIDC plans to lease out 16 plots, which measure a total of 2.3 lakh sqm, through the auction for establishment of industrial enterprises in Verna Industrial Estate.

news.title: Fire safety no less vital if building not highrise: Bombay HC
news.para: ​​A division bench of Justices Gautam Patel and Kamal Khata said, “Such a submission, if made, would be thoroughly irresponsible in a city like Mumbai.”

news.title: Site shows dip in registration of construction workers in Delhi
news.para: While workers’ unions claim the drop is due to loopholes in the online registration system, board officials say very few construction workers are turning up for registration.

news.title: Mumbai: Debris dumping boom as 6,000 buildings go for redevelopment
news.para: Across the city, though, residents, civic activists and environmentalists have complained about heaps of debris being mysteriously deposited in their neighbourhoods.

news.title: Guwahati civic body yet to recover Rs 110 crore property tax this fiscal: Mayor
news.para: The corporation is yet to collect over Rs 110 crore property tax in the current financial year, GMC commissioner Megha Nidhi Dahal said.

news.title: REITs, InvITs experience robust growth; fund mobilisation rises to Rs 11,474 crore in 2023
news.para: According to data compiled by Prime Database.com, REITs and InvITs collectively raised Rs 11,474 crore in 2023 compared to a record low amount of Rs 1,166 crore clocked in 2022.

news.title: Mysuru: Tenants unable to update details for Gruha Jyothi while shifting houses
news.para: Authorities warned that as Aadhaar is a legal document if the tenant fails to update the application details, it may lead to loss of benefit under the scheme.

news.title: MahaRERA plans three-tier audit of housing projects
news.para: As per this new mechanism, all the project registration applications received will be subjected to scrutiny at legal, financial, and technical levels. These three tiers of thorough scrutiny will be done by three different independent teams.

news.title: China urges better financing coordination for housing sector
news.para: The two regulators announced a plan to set up a mechanism aimed at responding to the financing needs of real estate projects more precisely, supporting the stable development of the housing sector, the regulators said in a joint statement on Friday.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board defers plans to levy fine on illegal constructions
news.para: As GHMC is already implementing this and earning crores in revenues through penalties, SCB planned to implement it in the Cantonment area, but a civilian nominated member in SCB and a BJP leader, J Rama Krishna, has stalled the plan.

news.title: Keystone Realtors sales bookings up 26% to Rs 1,423 crore in Apr-Dec 2023
news.para: According to a regulatory filing earlier this week, the company's sales bookings in volume terms rose 9 per cent to 0.82 million sq ft during the April-December period of this fiscal from 0.75 million sq ft in the year-ago period.

news.title: One held in Rs 24 crore fraud case on pretext of land sale near Noida Airport
news.para: The accused allegedly took Rs 24 crore from the victims with an assurance of getting them farmland near the airport. However, the land parcels were non-existent in reality, the complainants claimed.

news.title: Kolar flat owners see red over Bhopal civic body's 'green' eviction notice
news.para: But these senior citizens are now running from pillar to post after the Bhopal Municipal Corporation (BMC) slapped them with eviction notice in the month of December in the light of National Green Tribunal (NGT) order to remove encroachments in the area of 33 metres on both sides of Kaliasot river.

news.title: Ten booked for selling 24 acre Nagpur civic body's land worth Rs 140 crore
news.para: The encroachment on this land has obstructed the construction of the Sports Authority of India’s (SAI) regional centre in east Nagpur.

news.title: Rajasthan: Delay in release of PMAY-Gramin funds likely to be raised in review meeting
news.para: During the meeting, the state’s rural development department may raise the issue pertaining to delay in the release of the central share amounting to Rs 10.79 crore, along with the state share of Rs 261.17 crore.
